## About

This is a multiplayer tag game built with Godot {{ godot_version }}. Players move around the arena trying to tag each other while avoiding being tagged themselves.

## Features

- Multiple player support with controller and keyboard controls
- Tag mechanics with player tracking
- Smooth character movement and physics
- Bot players for single-player mode

## Movement Mechanics

- [x] Holding direction spins the ball
- [ ] Obstacles (walls, etc) bounce players
- [ ] Going outside the play area should rapidly slow you down, like sand or something

## Getting Started

1. Open `project.godot` in Godot {{ godot_version }} or later
2. Press F5 to run the game
3. Use WASD or arrow keys to move
4. Press space or controller buttons to dash

## Controls

### Player 0 (Keyboard)
- WASD: Movement
- Space: Dash

### Player 1-2 (Controllers)
- D-pad/Left stick: Movement
- A button: Dash

## Project Structure

- `main.tscn` - Main game scene
- `level.gd` - Level logic and game management
- `scenes/` - Player and game object scenes
- `utils/` - Utility scripts (camera, scoring, UI)

